The source speech material shows the old Sabian pattern worked when Host A had a distinct personality: deliberate, probing, forcing clarity, and Sabian had a distinct role: precise, verified, non-theatrical, no fluff.

Your own examples say the winning dynamic is: Host pushes for clarity, Sabian answers with execution, no vague language, no abstractions, no monologue.

So yes: the fix is to restore separate identities, separate jobs, and enforced rhythm.

